WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.367
[APPLAUSE]

00:00:06.187 --> 00:00:08.270
CHADE-MENG TAN: My friends,
thanks for being here.

00:00:08.270 --> 00:00:10.940
I recognize a few
faces-- some old friends,

00:00:10.940 --> 00:00:14.610
some from last week
when I was here.

00:00:14.610 --> 00:00:18.070
I want to start with success.

00:00:18.070 --> 00:00:20.340
There turns out to be a
surprising relationship

00:00:20.340 --> 00:00:23.410
between happiness and success.

00:00:23.410 --> 00:00:25.460
When I was growing
up in Singapore,

00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:28.900
right here in Singapore--
I mean, I'm Asian--

00:00:28.900 --> 00:00:32.720
and I was growing up, it was
drilled into my thick skull

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:35.810
that the relationship
between happiness and success

00:00:35.810 --> 00:00:39.130
is this, which is when someday,
when I become successful,

00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:41.820
I'll be happy.

00:00:41.820 --> 00:00:44.670
Therefore, for now, just suffer.

00:00:44.670 --> 00:00:47.690
Work hard, study hard,
suffer, suffer, suffer.

00:00:47.690 --> 00:00:49.840
Some day, when
you're successful,

00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:51.100
then you'll be happy.

00:00:51.100 --> 00:00:52.470
Yay.

00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:55.710
Things didn't quite
work that way.

00:00:55.710 --> 00:00:59.170
I think have a lot
of friends who--

00:00:59.170 --> 00:01:01.470
I'm sure you all do as
well-- I have friends who are

00:01:01.470 --> 00:01:04.849
very successful but miserable.

00:01:04.849 --> 00:01:07.780
And then I read the literature,
because all this has

00:01:07.780 --> 00:01:11.110
been researched for a
while, and the studies

00:01:11.110 --> 00:01:15.610
show that success leads
to happiness in only one

00:01:15.610 --> 00:01:18.590
situation, one and
only one situation,

00:01:18.590 --> 00:01:21.910
which is escape from poverty.

00:01:21.910 --> 00:01:25.350
So if you're poor, and then
you go from poor to not poor,

00:01:25.350 --> 00:01:28.340
so go from poor to middle
class, where you don't even

00:01:28.340 --> 00:01:31.039
worry about food or clothing
or shelter and so on,

00:01:31.039 --> 00:01:32.580
you go from poor to
not poor, there's

00:01:32.580 --> 00:01:36.000
a huge difference
in happiness levels.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:39.220
If you go from poor, sorry, if
you go from not poor to rich,

00:01:39.220 --> 00:01:42.530
so go from middle class
to rich, some difference.

00:01:42.530 --> 00:01:44.360
Not that much difference.

00:01:44.360 --> 00:01:50.101
If you go from rich to very
rich, even less difference.

00:01:50.101 --> 00:01:50.600
Why?

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:52.683
It turns out there's a
very simple explanation-- b

00:01:52.683 --> 00:01:55.500
because you only
have one body each.

00:01:55.500 --> 00:01:58.700
There's a limit to how
much you can consume.

00:01:58.700 --> 00:02:01.907
It's like a $2 hamburger
versus $100 caviar.

00:02:01.907 --> 00:02:02.740
Is there difference?

00:02:02.740 --> 00:02:03.630
Yes, some difference.

00:02:03.630 --> 00:02:04.700
Not that much difference.

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:08.280
$100 caviar, $1,000 caviar--
not that much difference, right?

00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:15.290
So there's kind of
an asymptotic peak.

00:02:15.290 --> 00:02:19.200
So a lot of my friends,
when they grew up,

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:21.290
they made sacrifices,
they become successful,

00:02:21.290 --> 00:02:23.590
and then they find that
they're sort of peaking

00:02:23.590 --> 00:02:26.990
and they keep earning more
money, but they're not happier,

00:02:26.990 --> 00:02:28.980
and in fact they're miserable.

00:02:28.980 --> 00:02:31.130
It turns out that
the reverse is true,

00:02:31.130 --> 00:02:37.180
which is that it turns out that
happiness leads to success.

00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:38.350
And that's fascinating.

00:02:38.350 --> 00:02:39.641
And there's even a word for it.

00:02:39.641 --> 00:02:42.480
The word is the
happiness advantage,

00:02:42.480 --> 00:02:46.960
which is that, for example,
our [INAUDIBLE] that happiness

00:02:46.960 --> 00:02:49.870
brings about is
conducive to success.

00:02:49.870 --> 00:02:53.200
For example, it turns
out that if you're happy,

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:57.900
you are 37% more
effective in sales.

00:02:57.900 --> 00:03:00.530
And retroactively, it make
sense, when you think about it.

00:03:00.530 --> 00:03:03.530
If there are two guys,
same price, same product,

00:03:03.530 --> 00:03:06.890
so everything equal, one guy
you see him, he's always happy,

00:03:06.890 --> 00:03:10.110
the other guy seems always
grumpy, who do you buy from?

00:03:10.110 --> 00:03:13.470
You buy from the first
guy 37% more of the time.

00:03:13.470 --> 00:03:14.750
So it's been quantified.

00:03:14.750 --> 00:03:17.208
I mean, the fact that it's been
quantified was fascinating.

00:03:19.034 --> 00:03:20.450
The other quality
is, for example,

00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:25.810
optimism, which relates
to job happiness.

00:03:25.810 --> 00:03:31.040
This was an early study
from Martin Seligman, who

00:03:31.040 --> 00:03:34.540
was a famous pioneer
in positive psychology,

00:03:34.540 --> 00:03:36.470
and this was the study
that made him famous.

00:03:36.470 --> 00:03:38.930
So the study was that
there was a lot turnover

00:03:38.930 --> 00:03:43.030
in insurance agents in MetLife.

00:03:43.030 --> 00:03:45.090
So in order to become
an insurance agent,

00:03:45.090 --> 00:03:48.010
you had to take a test, and
then you could pass a test,

00:03:48.010 --> 00:03:49.010
and you get a job.

00:03:49.010 --> 00:03:51.740
So there are people
who just failed a test,

00:03:51.740 --> 00:03:53.840
and Marty convinced
MetLife to hire

00:03:53.840 --> 00:03:57.330
those people, who, among
those people, who score high

00:03:57.330 --> 00:03:59.460
in optimism.

00:03:59.460 --> 00:04:01.730
And those will turn out to
outperform those who passed

00:04:01.730 --> 00:04:04.270
the test by a factor of 50%.

00:04:04.270 --> 00:04:06.370
That's fascinating.

00:04:06.370 --> 00:04:10.230
Happiness also causes you to
be more productive, according

00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:12.740
to studies, by about
30% because they

00:04:12.740 --> 00:04:15.820
seem to be more accurate
on their work by about 19%.

00:04:15.820 --> 00:04:20.769
It also correlates with good
health because of popularity,

00:04:20.769 --> 00:04:22.170
which is not surprising.

00:04:22.170 --> 00:04:23.837
Again, same thing,
your friend was

00:04:23.837 --> 00:04:25.670
always grumpy, your
friend was always happy,

00:04:25.670 --> 00:04:27.044
who do you want
to hang out with?

00:04:27.044 --> 00:04:29.150
That happy guy.

00:04:29.150 --> 00:04:31.825
And of course, popularity
also feeds back to success.

00:04:31.825 --> 00:04:34.635
If everybody loves you, long
term, they want to help you.

00:04:34.635 --> 00:04:35.760
They want to work with you.

00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:36.920
So you must accept.

00:04:36.920 --> 00:04:42.569
So this is the relationship--
success doesn't necessarily

00:04:42.569 --> 00:04:44.610
bring people happiness,
but in general, happiness

00:04:44.610 --> 00:04:46.490
does bring about success.

00:04:46.490 --> 00:04:52.040
So it makes sense to
learn to be happy.

00:04:52.040 --> 00:04:54.300
And because of-- everything
I just said, by the way,

00:04:54.300 --> 00:04:58.150
will be totally useless if it
turns out that happiness is

00:04:58.150 --> 00:05:00.350
something that we cannot
do anything about.

00:05:00.350 --> 00:05:02.450
You're born miserable
or you're born happy,

00:05:02.450 --> 00:05:04.910
and you're born
miserable, then I'm sorry,

00:05:04.910 --> 00:05:08.339
that sucks to be you.

00:05:08.339 --> 00:05:09.880
If that's the case,
everything I just

00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:11.880
said is not just
a waste of time,

00:05:11.880 --> 00:05:13.640
it's also very discouraging.

00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:16.760
So if I'm unhappy, I won't
be successful, right?

00:05:16.760 --> 00:05:19.790
It turns out one of the
most important things

00:05:19.790 --> 00:05:24.410
I ever learned in my
life is that happiness

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:26.900
is highly trainable.

00:05:26.900 --> 00:05:29.900
And the way happiness
is trainable--

00:05:29.900 --> 00:05:34.310
I move this over there so I
can move-- the way happiness is

00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:37.200
trainable is through joy.

00:05:37.200 --> 00:05:40.456
So first, what's the difference?

00:05:40.456 --> 00:05:42.080
For happiness, I'm
using the definition

00:05:42.080 --> 00:05:44.850
by Matthew Ricard, who is
known as the happiest man

00:05:44.850 --> 00:05:46.980
in the world.

00:05:46.980 --> 00:05:48.742
And he wrote a whole
book about happiness.

00:05:48.742 --> 00:05:51.200
And in his book, he defined
happiness like this-- happiness

00:05:51.200 --> 00:05:55.690
is defined as a deep
flourishing, a deep sense

00:05:55.690 --> 00:06:00.650
of flourishing that comes from
an exceptionally healthy mind,

00:06:00.650 --> 00:06:04.070
not a mode, not a
fleeting feeling,

00:06:04.070 --> 00:06:08.390
not an emotion, but an
optimal state of being.

00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:10.730
So there is happiness.

00:06:10.730 --> 00:06:14.430
In contrast, joy is
moment to moment.

00:06:14.430 --> 00:06:17.830
Joy is an emotion,
joy is fleeting.

00:06:17.830 --> 00:06:21.100
So it's a moment to
moment, there's an emotion.

00:06:21.100 --> 00:06:24.280
So the relationship
between the two-- happiness

00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:26.030
is something you
take-- it's kind

00:06:26.030 --> 00:06:29.710
of like integrate-- something
you integrate over time.

00:06:29.710 --> 00:06:32.560
But for example, you
say, have a happy day.

00:06:32.560 --> 00:06:34.930
Doesn't mean every
moment is nice.

00:06:34.930 --> 00:06:37.380
There are some moments
which are not so nice.

00:06:37.380 --> 00:06:40.020
For example, you kind
of miss your first train

00:06:40.020 --> 00:06:42.270
and you have to wait three
minutes for the next train,

00:06:42.270 --> 00:06:44.054
it's kinda annoying.

00:06:44.054 --> 00:06:46.470
And you were just having lunch,
minding your own business,

00:06:46.470 --> 00:06:49.300
and your friend forced you to
come here and listen to me,

00:06:49.300 --> 00:06:51.130
things like that.

00:06:51.130 --> 00:06:53.060
But then at the end
of the day you think,

00:06:53.060 --> 00:06:56.020
today is a happy day as a whole.

00:06:56.020 --> 00:06:57.220
So it's taken as a whole.

00:06:57.220 --> 00:06:59.300
In contrast, joy
is moment a moment.

00:06:59.300 --> 00:07:02.420
This moment is joyful,
this moment not.

00:07:02.420 --> 00:07:05.830
And the relationship is
that, therefore, happiness

00:07:05.830 --> 00:07:07.867
doesn't mean that
every moment is joyful.

00:07:07.867 --> 00:07:10.450
A happy life doesn't mean that
every moment in life be joyful.

00:07:10.450 --> 00:07:14.850
However, there is no such
thing as joyless happiness.

00:07:14.850 --> 00:07:19.210
Therefore, joy is the
building block of happiness.

00:07:19.210 --> 00:07:23.140
Therefore, if you
train to access joy,

00:07:23.140 --> 00:07:26.520
then you can build happiness.

00:07:26.520 --> 00:07:32.420
And it turns out access to
joy is highly trainable.

00:07:32.420 --> 00:07:35.000
And that was, to me, that
was the mind blowing part.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:39.620
You can train to
access joy on demand.

00:07:39.620 --> 00:07:41.120
But with sufficient
training, you

00:07:41.120 --> 00:07:47.840
can find it anytime, at
this, at any moment, joy.

00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:51.440
The question is, how?

00:07:51.440 --> 00:07:54.290
It turns out there are
very easy steps to do it.

00:07:54.290 --> 00:07:56.490
And there are three
steps to do this.

00:07:56.490 --> 00:08:02.390
The first step is
easing into joy.

00:08:02.390 --> 00:08:10.350
When it comes to easing,
the idea is to rest the mind

00:08:10.350 --> 00:08:13.270
Come on in, there's
seats over there.

00:08:13.270 --> 00:08:15.290
We were a little
worried that we wouldn't

00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:17.831
know enough people coming, so
we didn't have too many chairs.

00:08:21.070 --> 00:08:22.397
Now we need more chairs.

00:08:22.397 --> 00:08:24.230
And I can say that
because I'm the chairman.

00:08:24.230 --> 00:08:27.340
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:32.340 --> 00:08:32.919
Where was I?

00:08:32.919 --> 00:08:34.870
OK, easing.

00:08:34.870 --> 00:08:38.039
So easing is about
resting the mind.

00:08:38.039 --> 00:08:43.940
And then when the mind is
at rest, joy may arise.

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:47.010
And with enough training,
it becomes reliable.

00:08:47.010 --> 00:08:49.700
When the mind is at
rest, joy will arise.

00:08:49.700 --> 00:08:54.500
And when the joy arises, you use
the joy to reinforce the ease,

00:08:54.500 --> 00:08:59.480
because a joyful mind is a
mind at ease, easy to settle.

00:08:59.480 --> 00:09:02.320
And then, using the ease,
again, to reinforce the joy.

00:09:02.320 --> 00:09:05.920
And it becomes a very
powerful, virtuous cycle.

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:08.246
Shall we do a short experiment?

00:09:08.246 --> 00:09:09.620
This will only
take five seconds,

00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:14.210
so if you don't like it,
in five seconds, it's over.

00:09:14.210 --> 00:09:15.860
For five seconds,
I want to do this--

00:09:15.860 --> 00:09:19.250
I want to bring forward
tension to one breath.

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:23.630
So here's the instruction--
total but gentle attention

00:09:23.630 --> 00:09:27.270
to one breath, one in
breath, one out breath.

00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:28.910
And you're done.

00:09:28.910 --> 00:09:29.910
Sounds good?

00:09:29.910 --> 00:09:30.840
OK, beginning now.

00:09:41.510 --> 00:09:43.345
Thank you.

00:09:43.345 --> 00:09:44.970
How many of you,
after that one breath,

00:09:44.970 --> 00:09:47.700
find that you're a little
bit calmer, a little bit more

00:09:47.700 --> 00:09:49.277
relaxed than before the breath.

00:09:49.277 --> 00:09:50.360
Let's see a show of hands.

00:09:50.360 --> 00:09:51.670
Good, almost everybody.

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:56.510
Question-- why is
it so powerful?

00:09:56.510 --> 00:09:59.900
It's only one breath, how
does one breath already

00:09:59.900 --> 00:10:02.040
have an impact?

00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:04.400
There are two reasons,
one's physiological,

00:10:04.400 --> 00:10:06.070
one's psychological.

00:10:06.070 --> 00:10:09.070
The physiological reason is
that when you bring attention

00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:10.840
to one breath, do you
notice that you are

00:10:10.840 --> 00:10:13.990
breathing slower and deeper?

00:10:13.990 --> 00:10:17.130
And when you did that, you're
stimulating your vagus nerve.

00:10:17.130 --> 00:10:18.590
When you stimulate
the vagus nerve,

00:10:18.590 --> 00:10:21.980
you're activating something
called the relaxation response.

00:10:21.980 --> 00:10:24.030
And when you do that,
the relaxation response

00:10:24.030 --> 00:10:27.900
is the direct opposite
of the stress response.

00:10:27.900 --> 00:10:29.750
So therefore, in
the first breath,

00:10:29.750 --> 00:10:32.550
already your blood
pressure is going down,

00:10:32.550 --> 00:10:35.830
your heart rate is going down,
and your muscles are loosening,

00:10:35.830 --> 00:10:36.660
less tense.

00:10:36.660 --> 00:10:39.150
So already, in one breath,
you can feel the difference.

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:43.275
That is the
physiological effect.

00:10:43.275 --> 00:10:45.400
There's another effect
which is even more powerful,

00:10:45.400 --> 00:10:47.130
and that's a
psychological effect.

00:10:47.130 --> 00:10:52.600
Psychologically,
to be regretful,

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:55.170
you need to be in the past.

00:10:55.170 --> 00:10:59.680
To worry, you need
to be in the future.

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:03.010
When you bring total
attention to one breath,

00:11:03.010 --> 00:11:07.172
for the duration of one
breath, you are in the present,

00:11:07.172 --> 00:11:08.130
totally in the present.

00:11:08.130 --> 00:11:09.780
And because you are
totally in the present,

00:11:09.780 --> 00:11:11.696
you are not in the past
and not in the future,

00:11:11.696 --> 00:11:16.330
and therefore, you are
free from worry and regret.

00:11:16.330 --> 00:11:18.670
Freedom from worry
and regret, even

00:11:18.670 --> 00:11:22.540
for the duration of
one breath, that alone

00:11:22.540 --> 00:11:24.510
makes a difference, right?

00:11:24.510 --> 00:11:27.690
I think a lot of you are-- let
me see, probably 100% of you

00:11:27.690 --> 00:11:29.510
are high achievers.

00:11:29.510 --> 00:11:33.510
And some percentage of you are
people with big responsibility.

00:11:33.510 --> 00:11:37.100
So my guess is that
roughly 100% of you

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:42.220
are carrying worry and
regret all day every day.

00:11:42.220 --> 00:11:47.160
And in this one breath, you
get to release that load, even

00:11:47.160 --> 00:11:48.410
for just one breath.

00:11:48.410 --> 00:11:50.260
Then you bring it
back up, of course,

00:11:50.260 --> 00:11:56.779
but that one breath allows you
to recover, allows you to rest.

00:11:56.779 --> 00:11:58.320
So if you can do
this, we can sustain

00:11:58.320 --> 00:12:00.194
this for more than one
breath, three breaths,

00:12:00.194 --> 00:12:01.721
make it 15 seconds of rest.

00:12:01.721 --> 00:12:03.970
And then you can do it for
more than that, one minute,

00:12:03.970 --> 00:12:06.850
two minutes, and then your
body and mind get to rest.

00:12:06.850 --> 00:12:09.390
And that is how you get ease.

00:12:09.390 --> 00:12:13.000
And then, in the
ease, you find joy,

00:12:13.000 --> 00:12:15.200
because the mind is free
from worry and regret,

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:17.500
and there is a joyful
quality to this.

00:12:17.500 --> 00:12:22.185
So one question that comes often
is how powerful can this be?

00:12:22.185 --> 00:12:23.310
I'm going to take a moment.

00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:23.910
[BREATHES]

00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:24.410
OK.

00:12:24.410 --> 00:12:24.750
I'm a little bit better.

00:12:24.750 --> 00:12:25.458
Got back to work.

00:12:25.458 --> 00:12:27.430
Nothing changed.

00:12:27.430 --> 00:12:28.960
How powerful is this?

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:33.370
It turns out to be a lot more
powerful than even I expected.

00:12:33.370 --> 00:12:37.341
A long time ago, I read this
research on tennis players.

00:12:37.341 --> 00:12:38.840
So these are the
best tennis players

00:12:38.840 --> 00:12:41.160
in the world, those who
win the grand slams.

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.410
The question is, what
distinguishes them?

00:12:43.410 --> 00:12:45.490
And the quality that
distinguishes them

00:12:45.490 --> 00:12:46.720
was very surprising.

00:12:46.720 --> 00:12:52.630
It is the ability to rest
body and mine between points.

00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:54.960
So between points
there's 10 to 15 seconds.

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:58.760
And then they're able to use
the technique you just learned,

00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:00.660
but they master it
so they can rest body

00:13:00.660 --> 00:13:03.260
so that by the end
of 10 to 15 seconds,

00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:05.350
they are more
rested than before.

00:13:05.350 --> 00:13:08.890
And because of that, they
can sustain high performance

00:13:08.890 --> 00:13:13.080
over and over again, which is
how they win the grand slams.

00:13:13.080 --> 00:13:15.870
It was fascinating.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.240
So I read that.

00:13:18.240 --> 00:13:21.130
I was fascinated, but I couldn't
really write in the book

00:13:21.130 --> 00:13:25.020
because I haven't actually met
a world class tennis player,

00:13:25.020 --> 00:13:27.250
so I couldn't verify it.

00:13:27.250 --> 00:13:29.320
And then one fine
day, I met this guy,

00:13:29.320 --> 00:13:31.040
and his name is Novak.

00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:33.670
And Novak is, I don't know,
the best player in the history

00:13:33.670 --> 00:13:35.970
of a game or something.

00:13:35.970 --> 00:13:38.520
So I met him, we went
to initial courtesies,

00:13:38.520 --> 00:13:42.060
and then immediately, the first
question I asked him was this--

00:13:42.060 --> 00:13:46.380
I told him what I just told
you, and said, is it true?

00:13:46.380 --> 00:13:48.690
And Novak said yes, it's true.

00:13:48.690 --> 00:13:53.960
And he says, at my level, tennis
is no longer a physical game.

00:13:53.960 --> 00:13:55.830
Tennis is a mental game.

00:13:55.830 --> 00:13:59.040
And the secret to
winning is the ability

00:13:59.040 --> 00:14:03.460
to stay calm and
clear all the time.

00:14:03.460 --> 00:14:07.160
So this skill is a
very simple skill,

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:10.240
but the implication, at
least for success, is broad,

00:14:10.240 --> 00:14:11.880
is very broad and
very deep, right?

00:14:11.880 --> 00:14:14.177
It can make you the best
tennis player in the world.

00:14:14.177 --> 00:14:14.760
Not just that.

00:14:14.760 --> 00:14:17.000
It's also even for
office workers.

00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:19.670
It's obvious how well
it can do for you.

00:14:19.670 --> 00:14:21.570
And I think it does for you.

00:14:21.570 --> 00:14:25.690
This faculty is a
faculty of leadership.

00:14:25.690 --> 00:14:27.810
One important part of
leadership is the ability

00:14:27.810 --> 00:14:30.810
to think under fire,
especially in the military--

00:14:30.810 --> 00:14:32.640
in the military, and
in the police force,

00:14:32.640 --> 00:14:33.890
literally under fire.

00:14:33.890 --> 00:14:38.680
But in this case, figurative
under fire, in a crisis,

00:14:38.680 --> 00:14:42.530
if all your colleagues, all
your coworkers are panicking

00:14:42.530 --> 00:14:46.150
and you alone can think clearly,
then you are the leader.

00:14:48.740 --> 00:14:53.030
Everyone looks at you, and they
say, oh, that guy, [INAUDIBLE]

00:14:53.030 --> 00:14:56.285
[LAUGHTER]

00:14:58.610 --> 00:15:00.567
Right?

00:15:00.567 --> 00:15:02.150
I mean, some of us
are born with this,

00:15:02.150 --> 00:15:04.060
but it turns out it's
a trainable skill,

00:15:04.060 --> 00:15:06.518
and the training comes from
this-- it comes from an ability

00:15:06.518 --> 00:15:08.930
to calm the mind on demand.

00:15:08.930 --> 00:15:12.030
In addition, I think the
biggest impact of this

00:15:12.030 --> 00:15:17.880
is a consequence of--
it has to do with joy.

00:15:17.880 --> 00:15:20.162
When the mind-- when
you're able to bring

00:15:20.162 --> 00:15:21.870
the mind to a state
that's calm and clear

00:15:21.870 --> 00:15:28.160
and you do it on demand, you may
find-- or in my case, reliably,

00:15:28.160 --> 00:15:32.280
I find that I'm joyful, happy.

00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:37.550
And there was a time where even
once I got access reliably,

00:15:37.550 --> 00:15:41.130
so that means that every time
I sit in meditation, in two

00:15:41.130 --> 00:15:43.870
or three seconds,
I can get the joy.

00:15:43.870 --> 00:15:45.260
I didn't know why.

00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:46.850
It made no sense to me.

00:15:46.850 --> 00:15:50.500
Why would a calm and clear
mind always be joyful?

00:15:50.500 --> 00:15:52.200
So I asked around.

00:15:52.200 --> 00:15:55.010
One of my teachers gave
me a brilliant answer.

00:15:55.010 --> 00:15:56.400
And he said, it's very simple.

00:15:56.400 --> 00:15:58.880
Joy is the default
state of mind.

00:15:58.880 --> 00:16:02.870
Therefore, when the
mind is calm and clear,

00:16:02.870 --> 00:16:07.130
it returns to default. And
that's joy, simple as that.

00:16:07.130 --> 00:16:08.545
No magic, no mystery.

00:16:08.545 --> 00:16:09.440
I It's holy.

00:16:12.070 --> 00:16:15.100
That was a life
changing insight.

00:16:15.100 --> 00:16:17.760
And specifically--
so later on, I

00:16:17.760 --> 00:16:20.750
read up on the theory behind it.

00:16:20.750 --> 00:16:24.010
Specifically, there
is a quality of mind

00:16:24.010 --> 00:16:27.280
and a technical term in the
Pali language-- it's sukha,

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:33.380
S U K H A. Sukha is a quality
of mind as defined as quiet joy,

00:16:33.380 --> 00:16:35.279
oh, sorry,
non-energetic joy, joy

00:16:35.279 --> 00:16:36.445
that doesn't require energy.

00:16:39.650 --> 00:16:42.290
It has two characteristics--
because it doesn't require

00:16:42.290 --> 00:16:44.850
energy, I compare it
to the hum of the air

00:16:44.850 --> 00:16:46.990
conditioning in the room.

00:16:46.990 --> 00:16:50.430
The hum is always there, but
normally you don't notice.

00:16:50.430 --> 00:16:52.480
The only way to
notice the hum is

00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:55.932
to quiet down and pay attention.

00:16:55.932 --> 00:16:58.390
And once you hear that, you
find it's always there, and has

00:16:58.390 --> 00:17:04.520
always been there, and always
will be there-- very annoying

00:17:04.520 --> 00:17:06.280
Sukha is the same.

00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:09.260
It's a quality of mind as
always there, always been there.

00:17:09.260 --> 00:17:12.000
Are so the first thing
about non-energetic joy,

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:14.550
non-energetic means
it's very subtle.

00:17:14.550 --> 00:17:17.300
Because it's very subtle,
the only way to access it

00:17:17.300 --> 00:17:19.710
is quiet down and pay attention.

00:17:19.710 --> 00:17:22.510
Second characteristic--
because it's non-energetic,

00:17:22.510 --> 00:17:26.430
it is extremely sustainable.

00:17:26.430 --> 00:17:29.550
Once you learn to access it,
you find that it's always there.

00:17:29.550 --> 00:17:31.760
It's always there for you.

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:35.410
And then you have a
reliable source of joy

00:17:35.410 --> 00:17:39.720
to-- what do you call it--
it's called bringing water

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:40.310
from a well.

00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:46.990
Anyway, to get the benefit
from, any time of day, any day.

00:17:46.990 --> 00:17:50.360
And that is life changing,
because we go through life

00:17:50.360 --> 00:17:51.960
thinking we need to
pursue happiness,

00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:53.834
and you see even in the
American Constitution

00:17:53.834 --> 00:17:55.130
the pursuit of happiness.

00:17:55.130 --> 00:17:57.200
And then when we
go through this,

00:17:57.200 --> 00:18:00.690
we realize that happiness is not
something you need to pursue.

00:18:00.690 --> 00:18:03.130
Happiness is already
there, it's something

00:18:03.130 --> 00:18:04.670
we just have to allow.

00:18:04.670 --> 00:18:08.210
And once you can
access it, we are free,

00:18:08.210 --> 00:18:10.770
we have freedom, we are
free from being bonded

00:18:10.770 --> 00:18:13.320
by what we have to
do to become happy,

00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:14.680
because we're already happy.

00:18:14.680 --> 00:18:18.220
So now we can do what
is the right thing.

00:18:18.220 --> 00:18:20.910
So that changed my life.

00:18:20.910 --> 00:18:22.000
And that is only step one.

00:18:24.820 --> 00:18:25.804
But wait, there's more.

00:18:25.804 --> 00:18:27.470
If you buy it now you
get two more steps

00:18:27.470 --> 00:18:29.371
for $19.99 plus
