00:18:29.371 --> 00:18:32.668
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:35.970 --> 00:18:37.965
It's another [INAUDIBLE]
by the way, which is

00:18:37.965 --> 00:18:40.860
it raises baseline happiness.

00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:45.370
So for me, my own
experience is--

00:18:45.370 --> 00:18:49.380
let me check my time-- my own
experience is when I was young,

00:18:49.380 --> 00:18:51.361
I was miserable.

00:18:51.361 --> 00:18:52.360
I think it was genetics.

00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:56.370
Genetically, I was born with a
low baseline, a low happiness

00:18:56.370 --> 00:18:56.887
baseline.

00:18:56.887 --> 00:18:59.220
And I'm one of those people
who, when they were injured,

00:18:59.220 --> 00:19:02.380
looked at my chart before
I was born, say, sorry,

00:19:02.380 --> 00:19:05.300
sucks to be you, sorry.

00:19:05.300 --> 00:19:05.880
Goodbye, bro.

00:19:08.710 --> 00:19:12.170
So the way I experienced it
is that if nothing happens,

00:19:12.170 --> 00:19:13.967
I was miserable.

00:19:13.967 --> 00:19:15.800
And then something good
had to happen for me

00:19:15.800 --> 00:19:18.350
to not be miserable, but that
only last a short while, couple

00:19:18.350 --> 00:19:20.070
days or whatever,
couple hours, and then

00:19:20.070 --> 00:19:22.910
back to being miserable,
I'm always miserable.

00:19:22.910 --> 00:19:26.200
And a couple years later,
I discovered the reverse.

00:19:26.200 --> 00:19:28.750
I discover I'm always happy.

00:19:28.750 --> 00:19:31.550
My baseline happiness shifted.

00:19:31.550 --> 00:19:33.780
Nothing happens, I'm jolly.

00:19:33.780 --> 00:19:36.710
In fact, I became a
jolly good fellow.

00:19:36.710 --> 00:19:37.542
It's fascinating.

00:19:37.542 --> 00:19:38.250
And what changed?

00:19:38.250 --> 00:19:40.940
What change was this,
was finding sukha,

00:19:40.940 --> 00:19:43.819
getting reliable access to
it, and then, eventually,

00:19:43.819 --> 00:19:45.860
my happiness baseline just
kept moving up and up.

00:19:45.860 --> 00:19:47.770
And before I knew it,
it crept up all the way

00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:51.530
from one side of the
spectrum to the other side.

00:19:51.530 --> 00:19:53.490
But anyway, that's
only step one.

00:19:53.490 --> 00:19:56.670
Step two is inclining
the mind to what?

00:19:56.670 --> 00:19:58.420
Joy.

00:19:58.420 --> 00:20:00.200
So what does that mean?

00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:03.790
The word inclining here
refers to mental inclination,

00:20:03.790 --> 00:20:05.480
changing mental inclination.

00:20:05.480 --> 00:20:10.140
So in the old texts, in
the ancient scriptures,

00:20:10.140 --> 00:20:14.860
mental inclination is compared
to the slope of a mountain.

00:20:14.860 --> 00:20:18.770
When a mountain is sloped in a
certain way, when water flows,

00:20:18.770 --> 00:20:23.260
it flows effortlessly
in that direction.

00:20:23.260 --> 00:20:24.910
Same thing with the mind.

00:20:24.910 --> 00:20:27.790
If the mind is inclined
towards a certain way,

00:20:27.790 --> 00:20:30.820
mental experiences
flow effortlessly

00:20:30.820 --> 00:20:32.530
towards a direction.

00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:35.890
For example, if you are
inclined towards anger,

00:20:35.890 --> 00:20:40.060
every other thing makes
you angry effortlessly.

00:20:40.060 --> 00:20:43.430
But if your mind is
inclined towards joy,

00:20:43.430 --> 00:20:47.370
every other thing
makes you joyful.

00:20:47.370 --> 00:20:52.430
The question is, is it possible
to change in condition of mind?

00:20:52.430 --> 00:20:53.740
Turns out it's yes.

00:20:53.740 --> 00:20:55.490
And the other question is how?

00:20:55.490 --> 00:20:56.670
If yes, how?

00:20:56.670 --> 00:20:59.310
Turns out, again, one
of the surprises for me

00:20:59.310 --> 00:21:03.660
was that the methodology is
actually very, very simple.

00:21:03.660 --> 00:21:06.220
One of the most effective
ways, and simplest

00:21:06.220 --> 00:21:14.030
and most powerful ways is to
notice thin slices of joy.

00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:14.700
That is all.

00:21:14.700 --> 00:21:16.586
So what does that mean?

00:21:16.586 --> 00:21:18.710
In life, in day to day
life, moment to moment life,

00:21:18.710 --> 00:21:21.590
you notice that thin slices of
joy everywhere, all the time.

00:21:21.590 --> 00:21:29.150
For example, when I'm
thirsty, I drink water.

00:21:29.150 --> 00:21:32.410
That was nice.

00:21:32.410 --> 00:21:34.520
I just experienced
a thin slice of joy.

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:36.010
It's thin in two dimensions.

00:21:36.010 --> 00:21:39.592
The first is thin spatially,
so it wasn't like, yay,

00:21:39.592 --> 00:21:41.436
it was like, eh.

00:21:41.436 --> 00:21:43.750
[LAUGHTER]

00:21:43.750 --> 00:21:48.210
Second, it lasted only two
seconds, maybe three seconds,

00:21:48.210 --> 00:21:49.910
didn't last that long.

00:21:49.910 --> 00:21:53.784
And because they're so thin,
we miss them all the time.

00:21:53.784 --> 00:21:55.000
We miss them all the time.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:56.790
And therefore, we
look at our days,

00:21:56.790 --> 00:21:59.660
say, this day I was miserable,
no joy at all, because we

00:21:59.660 --> 00:22:01.840
didn't see all these things.

00:22:01.840 --> 00:22:03.400
What if you see that?

00:22:03.400 --> 00:22:06.250
So let's say we play a
game, right, we play a game.

00:22:06.250 --> 00:22:08.375
Let's say we count the
number of blue cars,

00:22:08.375 --> 00:22:11.000
and those who count the highest
number of blue cars in one week

00:22:11.000 --> 00:22:12.110
wins a prize.

00:22:12.110 --> 00:22:13.280
I give you a prize.

00:22:13.280 --> 00:22:14.915
So, OK, what's the prize?

00:22:14.915 --> 00:22:16.290
At first, I was
going to give you

00:22:16.290 --> 00:22:20.262
a bell, by then I think to
myself, no bell, please.

00:22:20.262 --> 00:22:21.720
So you get a no
bell, please prize.

00:22:21.720 --> 00:22:22.934
[LAUGHTER]

00:22:22.934 --> 00:22:25.600
It was very funny when I said it
in front of a Nobel Peace Prize

00:22:25.600 --> 00:22:27.210
winner.

00:22:27.210 --> 00:22:28.710
She thought it was very funny.

00:22:28.710 --> 00:22:31.330
Anyway, we play the game.

00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:32.785
What would happen after that?

00:22:32.785 --> 00:22:35.035
If you played the game, you
find that you-- first, you

00:22:35.035 --> 00:22:36.950
start noticing blue
cars, one car, two cars,

00:22:36.950 --> 00:22:39.450
and you find it everywhere,
every time you're in traffic,

00:22:39.450 --> 00:22:42.880
you see blue cars everywhere,
never noticed them before.

00:22:42.880 --> 00:22:44.240
Same thing here.

00:22:44.240 --> 00:22:46.490
When you start noticing
thin slices of joy,

00:22:46.490 --> 00:22:49.190
you start to find every way.

00:22:49.190 --> 00:22:53.140
Every drink of water,
there's a thin slice of joy.

00:22:53.140 --> 00:22:56.940
Every meal, at least
the very first bite, oh,

00:22:56.940 --> 00:22:58.790
delicious, thin slice of joy.

00:22:58.790 --> 00:23:01.340
You meet an old friend,
there's a thin slice of joy,

00:23:01.340 --> 00:23:05.760
and new friend,
thing slice of joy.

00:23:05.760 --> 00:23:10.430
Even simple things like
walking, walking without pain.

00:23:10.430 --> 00:23:13.549
Seeing the beautiful sight.

00:23:13.549 --> 00:23:15.590
You notice I was standing
there when you came in,

00:23:15.590 --> 00:23:16.394
looking at a sight.

00:23:16.394 --> 00:23:17.810
I mean, I've been
here many times,

00:23:17.810 --> 00:23:20.640
but still, these lights are joy.

00:23:23.320 --> 00:23:25.010
Can I assign
homework, by the way?

00:23:25.010 --> 00:23:26.260
This is the homework.

00:23:26.260 --> 00:23:29.740
Homework-- I want you to
notice thin slices of joy

00:23:29.740 --> 00:23:32.480
in daily life.

00:23:32.480 --> 00:23:37.150
When you're eating, the very
first bite, the very first bite

00:23:37.150 --> 00:23:38.830
is the most delicious.

00:23:38.830 --> 00:23:41.150
So at the very first
bite, bring full attention

00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:44.580
to the joy of taste.

00:23:44.580 --> 00:23:46.240
Sounds good?

00:23:46.240 --> 00:23:49.420
Every time you see a friend,
bring one moment of attention

00:23:49.420 --> 00:23:52.330
to the joy of seeing a friend.

00:23:52.330 --> 00:23:57.140
When you have a shower,
the first contact of water,

00:23:57.140 --> 00:23:59.100
one moment of joy.

00:23:59.100 --> 00:24:01.090
When drinking water,
one moment of joy.

00:24:01.090 --> 00:24:03.320
Can you do that?

00:24:03.320 --> 00:24:04.700
Let's see what happens.

00:24:04.700 --> 00:24:06.533
If you do it for a few
days, I guarantee you

00:24:06.533 --> 00:24:07.620
it will change your life.

00:24:07.620 --> 00:24:10.700
You'll be happier.

00:24:10.700 --> 00:24:14.750
So the first effect of that
is that if you find more joy,

00:24:14.750 --> 00:24:17.382
your joy doubles--
nothing changes,

00:24:17.382 --> 00:24:18.840
your life remains
exactly the same,

00:24:18.840 --> 00:24:22.190
your joy doubles already
just by noticing.

00:24:22.190 --> 00:24:23.920
However, there is
another effect which

00:24:23.920 --> 00:24:26.530
is even more powerful
if you do this,

00:24:26.530 --> 00:24:29.330
which is the familiarization.

00:24:29.330 --> 00:24:32.300
When the mind starts
to see joy a lot,

00:24:32.300 --> 00:24:35.450
the mind becomes
familiar with joy.

00:24:35.450 --> 00:24:38.860
And the word familiar is
related closely related

00:24:38.860 --> 00:24:41.100
to the word family.

00:24:41.100 --> 00:24:45.210
So the joy becomes a member
of our family, somebody

00:24:45.210 --> 00:24:47.200
who is always there
for you, somebody

00:24:47.200 --> 00:24:49.620
you can always count on.

00:24:49.620 --> 00:24:54.420
And then, because of that, joy
becomes an inclination of mine.

00:24:54.420 --> 00:24:59.672
And once inclined, every
other experience is joyful.

00:24:59.672 --> 00:25:01.380
Fascination-- it
doesn't take extra time,

00:25:01.380 --> 00:25:05.251
doesn't [INAUDIBLE] how
to do and that's step two.

00:25:05.251 --> 00:25:08.130
Step three is
uplifting the mind,

00:25:08.130 --> 00:25:11.610
uplifting the mind
specifically with goodness.

00:25:11.610 --> 00:25:14.230
Let's see, shall we
try another experiment?

00:25:14.230 --> 00:25:17.040
OK, this one is twice as
long as the previous one.

00:25:17.040 --> 00:25:19.835
This one is 10 seconds.

00:25:19.835 --> 00:25:21.460
For 10 seconds-- and
I like to do this,

00:25:21.460 --> 00:25:25.370
I like to secretly identify
two people in this room,

00:25:25.370 --> 00:25:28.500
and in secret, think, I wish
for that person to be happy.

00:25:28.500 --> 00:25:30.230
And I wish for that
person to be happy.

00:25:30.230 --> 00:25:36.010
Just think, don't do
anything, don't say anything,

00:25:36.010 --> 00:25:37.330
don't go, like, ooh.

00:25:37.330 --> 00:25:40.810
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:40.810 --> 00:25:41.812
No, HR is safe.

00:25:44.690 --> 00:25:49.310
Just think-- this is an
entirely thinking exercise.

00:25:49.310 --> 00:25:50.430
Sounds good?

