If that's true,
you may have just

00:26:21.910 --> 00:26:25.890
discovered one of the most
important secrets of happiness,

00:26:25.890 --> 00:26:30.410
to be on the giving end of a
kind thought is intrinsically

00:26:30.410 --> 00:26:31.360
rewarding.

00:26:31.360 --> 00:26:34.267
Therefore, all you had to
do is bring up a thought.

00:26:34.267 --> 00:26:35.600
I wish for that guy to be happy.

00:26:35.600 --> 00:26:38.350
That alone makes you
a little happier.

00:26:38.350 --> 00:26:42.630
If you do that a lot, it
makes you much happier.

00:26:42.630 --> 00:26:44.770
How powerful is this?

00:26:44.770 --> 00:26:47.180
How far can I scale this?

00:26:47.180 --> 00:26:50.630
I was once giving a talk
on a Monday evening,

00:26:50.630 --> 00:26:53.600
and then I assigned--
so we did this exercise,

00:26:53.600 --> 00:26:56.419
and I assign homework, by the
way, again, second homework.

00:26:56.419 --> 00:26:58.960
OK, I'll tell you what I did,
and then, this is the homework.

00:26:58.960 --> 00:27:04.420
The homework is this-- during
the workday, every hour,

00:27:04.420 --> 00:27:08.170
spend 10 seconds on the hour,
spend 10 seconds wishing

00:27:08.170 --> 00:27:10.710
for two people outside
your cubicle or office,

00:27:10.710 --> 00:27:12.764
wish them to be
happy in your head.

00:27:12.764 --> 00:27:14.430
So not embarrassing,
right, because they

00:27:14.430 --> 00:27:16.888
don't know what you're thinking,
as long as you don't do it

00:27:16.888 --> 00:27:17.990
like, eh.

00:27:17.990 --> 00:27:20.326
Then that would be embarrassing.

00:27:20.326 --> 00:27:21.450
They'll think you're weird.

00:27:21.450 --> 00:27:23.750
Unless you're in Google,
then you're not so weird.

00:27:23.750 --> 00:27:26.530
Nah, just kidding.

00:27:26.530 --> 00:27:29.890
But just thinking, and
then, nobody knows anything,

00:27:29.890 --> 00:27:31.300
and then go back to work.

00:27:31.300 --> 00:27:32.720
See what happens.

00:27:32.720 --> 00:27:33.470
Shall we try that?

00:27:33.470 --> 00:27:34.830
At least tomorrow?

00:27:34.830 --> 00:27:36.010
OK.

00:27:36.010 --> 00:27:38.260
So I assigned this
homework on a Monday

00:27:38.260 --> 00:27:41.770
for an audience about twice
this size, I assigned homework.

00:27:41.770 --> 00:27:43.700
And that was a Monday evening.

00:27:43.700 --> 00:27:47.250
Wednesday morning, I received
an email from a total stranger.

00:27:47.250 --> 00:27:50.070
And this person
said, I hate my job.

00:27:50.070 --> 00:27:54.030
I hate coming to work
every single day.

00:27:54.030 --> 00:27:57.020
But I did the
homework on Tuesday,

00:27:57.020 --> 00:28:00.960
and Tuesday was my happiest
day in seven years--

00:28:00.960 --> 00:28:02.520
happiest day in seven years.

00:28:02.520 --> 00:28:03.270
What do you think?

00:28:03.270 --> 00:28:06.850
It took 80 seconds of thinking.

00:28:06.850 --> 00:28:09.840
It's fascinating.

00:28:09.840 --> 00:28:13.380
One of the important
things about this thinking

00:28:13.380 --> 00:28:17.380
is that this is easier than
the other exercises, I think.

00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:17.880
Why?

00:28:17.880 --> 00:28:20.320
Because the other exercises--
like resting the mind,

00:28:20.320 --> 00:28:23.690
you kind of need a little
bit of practice to rest.

00:28:23.690 --> 00:28:27.950
There people who cannot rest,
like they have to practice,

00:28:27.950 --> 00:28:31.790
but inclining the mind, again,
kind of takes a little bit

00:28:31.790 --> 00:28:34.110
of practice, like, do
it over one or two days,

00:28:34.110 --> 00:28:37.590
and you start to get a groove.

00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:39.401
But this exercise,
loving kindness,

00:28:39.401 --> 00:28:41.150
to be on the giving
end of a kind thought,

00:28:41.150 --> 00:28:45.010
all it takes is the
arising of a thought.

00:28:45.010 --> 00:28:47.980
And every single adult
I ever knew in my life--

00:28:47.980 --> 00:28:50.152
every adult knows how
to bring up a thought.

00:28:50.152 --> 00:28:52.110
And bringing up a thought
is the simplest thing

00:28:52.110 --> 00:28:53.660
any adult can do.

00:28:53.660 --> 00:28:56.050
Everybody think of an elephant.

00:28:56.050 --> 00:28:58.340
Everybody can do that,
easily, effortlessly.

00:28:58.340 --> 00:29:02.370
So therefore, if all it takes
to have an injection of joy

00:29:02.370 --> 00:29:08.610
is to bring up a thought, you
can't get easier than that.

00:29:08.610 --> 00:29:10.360
So by the way, this
is so powerful,

00:29:10.360 --> 00:29:12.766
I would say that if you
don't remember a single thing

00:29:12.766 --> 00:29:14.265
in this lecture,
or rather, you only

00:29:14.265 --> 00:29:16.754
remember one thing
from this lecture,

00:29:16.754 --> 00:29:18.045
remember how good looking I am.

00:29:18.045 --> 00:29:19.340
[LAUGHTER]

00:29:19.340 --> 00:29:22.500
If you remember two things in
this lecture, remembered this.

00:29:22.500 --> 00:29:23.484
No, I'm just kidding.

00:29:23.484 --> 00:29:25.150
Remember only one
thing in this lecture,

00:29:25.150 --> 00:29:27.520
remember this exercise--
wishing for others

00:29:27.520 --> 00:29:29.770
to be happy in your head.

00:29:29.770 --> 00:29:31.825
This alone guarantees
an increase

00:29:31.825 --> 00:29:35.720
in happiness and no cost.

00:29:35.720 --> 00:29:37.390
So if you do this, this is it.

00:29:37.390 --> 00:29:40.370
The three steps.

00:29:40.370 --> 00:29:43.360
If you do this over time,
practicing over time,

00:29:43.360 --> 00:29:45.510
three things happen.

00:29:45.510 --> 00:29:49.550
The first thing that happens
is that joyful experiences

00:29:49.550 --> 00:29:52.360
in your life gets
even more joyful,

00:29:52.360 --> 00:29:54.430
and by now, it's obvious
why, because you've

00:29:54.430 --> 00:29:56.020
been paying attention to it.

00:29:56.020 --> 00:29:58.900
Previously, eating food
is eh, kind of nice,

00:29:58.900 --> 00:30:01.080
but now it's, ooh,
this is delicious.

00:30:01.080 --> 00:30:01.580
Right?

00:30:01.580 --> 00:30:04.180
Even for one moment,
like, you double your joy

00:30:04.180 --> 00:30:07.840
at no cost whatsoever,
no extra cost whatsoever.

00:30:07.840 --> 00:30:10.070
So that's the first
effect, joyful experiences

00:30:10.070 --> 00:30:11.460
become even more joyful.

00:30:11.460 --> 00:30:16.970
The second effect is
that new true experiences

00:30:16.970 --> 00:30:20.970
become joyful experiences, more
and more so, increasingly so.

00:30:20.970 --> 00:30:21.860
Why?

00:30:21.860 --> 00:30:25.950
Because you stop taking
them for granted.

00:30:25.950 --> 00:30:29.140
So it's like suddenly,
simple things

00:30:29.140 --> 00:30:32.160
like having access to water,
at first it's kind of neutral,

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:33.390
water, whatever.

00:30:33.390 --> 00:30:35.624
But now it's like, oh my
God, this is so valuable.

00:30:35.624 --> 00:30:37.790
So many people in the world
have no access to water.

00:30:37.790 --> 00:30:39.500
I have it.

00:30:39.500 --> 00:30:41.090
And then it goes
to something else.

00:30:41.090 --> 00:30:47.210
You start to find joy
in the absence of pain.

00:30:47.210 --> 00:30:50.316
To be free from
pain is so joyful.

00:30:50.316 --> 00:30:51.940
When I have a toothache,
I tell myself,

00:30:51.940 --> 00:30:54.089
if I didn't have this
toothache, I'd be so happy.

00:30:54.089 --> 00:30:56.380
And then I went to see a
dentist, this thing went away,

00:30:56.380 --> 00:31:00.130
and then, three days later,
I forget to be happy.

00:31:00.130 --> 00:31:01.900
What if I never
forget I'm happy?

00:31:01.900 --> 00:31:04.280
This moment right here and
right now, I'm not in pain.

00:31:04.280 --> 00:31:06.200
This moment, I can walk.

00:31:06.200 --> 00:31:09.890
Not just I can walk, I
can walk without pain.

00:31:09.890 --> 00:31:15.570
Freedom from pain is such a
valuable, beautiful experience.

00:31:15.570 --> 00:31:18.600
Suddenly, you stop
taking it for granted.

00:31:18.600 --> 00:31:21.220
And that's how
what was originally

00:31:21.220 --> 00:31:24.420
we thought to be
neutral become joyful.

00:31:24.420 --> 00:31:26.660
And I think one of the
key words is gratefulness.

00:31:26.660 --> 00:31:30.140
We start becoming
grateful for everything.

00:31:30.140 --> 00:31:32.520
And I've heard there's
a Mayan practice I just

00:31:32.520 --> 00:31:33.900
learned last week.

00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:36.110
The old Mayan practice
is to wake up every day

00:31:36.110 --> 00:31:38.500
and say thank you 400 times.

00:31:38.500 --> 00:31:41.580
So a Mayan practitioner,
the moment she wakes up,

00:31:41.580 --> 00:31:44.570
she breathes in the air,
and she says, thank you air.

00:31:44.570 --> 00:31:46.500
She sees the ground,
thank you ground.

00:31:46.500 --> 00:31:49.960
I mean, generally thanking
everything 400 times a day.

00:31:49.960 --> 00:31:51.610
That's a key to happiness.

00:31:51.610 --> 00:31:55.100
And this skews
[INAUDIBLE] naturally,

00:31:55.100 --> 00:31:57.820
effortlessly bring you there.

00:31:57.820 --> 00:31:59.124
So that's the second effect.

00:31:59.124 --> 00:32:00.540
The third effect
is, I think, even

00:32:00.540 --> 00:32:02.990
more powerful than
the first two, which

00:32:02.990 --> 00:32:08.620
is that painful experiences
become manageable.

00:32:08.620 --> 00:32:11.180
Why so?

00:32:11.180 --> 00:32:13.580
The first reason is
that all the skills

00:32:13.580 --> 00:32:17.510
you learn to increase
joy turn out to also--

00:32:17.510 --> 00:32:21.170
you can apply directly
to dealing with pain.

00:32:21.170 --> 00:32:23.920
For example, in a
difficult situation,

00:32:23.920 --> 00:32:25.750
emotionally difficult,
you can learn

00:32:25.750 --> 00:32:28.240
to calm the mind on demand.

00:32:28.240 --> 00:32:31.320
If you can calm the mind,
already half the problem

00:32:31.320 --> 00:32:33.370
gets solved on the spot.

00:32:33.370 --> 00:32:33.960
That's one.

00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:36.100
So everything you learn
is directly applicable.

00:32:36.100 --> 00:32:41.010
More than that, which is a
very powerful effect, which

00:32:41.010 --> 00:32:43.280
I kind of discovered
by accident,

00:32:43.280 --> 00:32:45.920
and what I did-- I thought
I was going crazy--

00:32:45.920 --> 00:32:49.900
I discovered that I
was able to access joy

00:32:49.900 --> 00:32:53.600
in the midst of great pain.

00:32:53.600 --> 00:32:57.180
So I was going through
a long episode of pain,

00:32:57.180 --> 00:33:03.370
emotional pain, and I found
that at least once a day,

00:33:03.370 --> 00:33:08.650
a couple times a day, I felt
joyful, adulterated joy,

00:33:08.650 --> 00:33:12.110
like, yay kind of
joy from nothing.

00:33:12.110 --> 00:33:13.750
I was just walking
around, just eating

00:33:13.750 --> 00:33:15.580
my food, meeting
friends, saying hi

00:33:15.580 --> 00:33:17.520
to friends, things like that.

00:33:17.520 --> 00:33:20.100
Suddenly, I just
became very joyful.

00:33:20.100 --> 00:33:25.790
And I was like, wait a minute,
one moment I was so miserable,

00:33:25.790 --> 00:33:29.180
I'm going to die, and
then suddenly, I have joy

00:33:29.180 --> 00:33:30.780
lasting for about five minutes.

00:33:30.780 --> 00:33:34.520
And then, I was so
miserable, I'm going to die.

00:33:34.520 --> 00:33:36.561
I thought I was going
crazy, more than before,

00:33:36.561 --> 00:33:37.560
I mean, more than usual.

00:33:40.100 --> 00:33:41.177
What happened?

00:33:41.177 --> 00:33:42.010
I learned something.

00:33:42.010 --> 00:33:49.010
I learned that joy and pain
are not mutually soluble.

00:33:49.010 --> 00:33:50.520
They can displace each other.

00:33:50.520 --> 00:33:52.240
So if one is much
bigger than the other,

00:33:52.240 --> 00:33:54.531
there's a lot of joy, but a
little bit of pain, the joy

00:33:54.531 --> 00:33:56.010
displaces the pain,
and vice-versa.

00:33:56.010 --> 00:33:57.710
But they are
equally strong, they

00:33:57.710 --> 00:33:59.210
do not dissolve each other.

00:33:59.210 --> 00:34:01.420
They exist side by side.

00:34:01.420 --> 00:34:07.150
And the person I learned
most of this from

00:34:07.150 --> 00:34:10.800
is this woman called
Rigoberta Menchu.

00:34:10.800 --> 00:34:13.360
Rigoberta is Mayan, so
the mayan thank yous

00:34:13.360 --> 00:34:15.600
I learned from her as well.

00:34:15.600 --> 00:34:17.980
Rigoberta is a
Mayan woman, she's

00:34:17.980 --> 00:34:21.659
the first Mayan ever to
win the Nobel Peace Prize.

00:34:21.659 --> 00:34:24.030
And by the way, has anybody
here met a Nobel Peace Prize

00:34:24.030 --> 00:34:25.699
winner before?

00:34:25.699 --> 00:34:28.489
I met a few.

00:34:28.489 --> 00:34:30.139
There's a stereotype.

00:34:30.139 --> 00:34:34.540
The stereotype is-- I mean, the
guy won a Nobel Peace Prize,

00:34:34.540 --> 00:34:36.010
he must be nice, right?

00:34:36.010 --> 00:34:37.570
So you see this
person, you expect

00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:40.920
him or her to be warm and
say, hey, how are you doing?

00:34:40.920 --> 00:34:44.469
To be nice to you and
so on and so forth.

00:34:44.469 --> 00:34:49.810
Rigoberta fits the
stereotype to a T.

00:34:49.810 --> 00:34:51.190
You meet her, even
at a distance,

00:34:51.190 --> 00:34:53.909
even with the language
barrier-- she speaks Spanish.

00:34:53.909 --> 00:34:56.429
You have to go through
interpreter half the time,

00:34:56.429 --> 00:34:58.710
even with that, you see
her immediately, you

00:34:58.710 --> 00:35:01.060
can feel her goodness.

00:35:01.060 --> 00:35:03.807
And then you ask for-- and
then she sees you, says hey.

00:35:03.807 --> 00:35:05.890
And then you ask for a
hug-- of course, of course.

00:35:05.890 --> 00:35:08.070
And she's always happy,
she's always nice.

00:35:11.020 --> 00:35:12.950
I spent an hour with her.

00:35:12.950 --> 00:35:16.230
And within one hour, I
realized that there's

00:35:16.230 --> 00:35:21.700
something below the surface,
that she has a lot of pain,

00:35:21.700 --> 00:35:25.360
a huge amount of pain.

00:35:25.360 --> 00:35:28.245
Her pain comes from her
life, her life trauma.

00:35:31.440 --> 00:35:35.030
Her father was burned
alive by the government.

00:35:35.030 --> 00:35:40.660
Her mom was kidnapped,
tortured, raped, murdered,

00:35:40.660 --> 00:35:43.240
and her body was left on
the side of the street

00:35:43.240 --> 00:35:46.480
to feed the wild animals.

00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:48.520
She lost her brother
in a similar way.

00:35:48.520 --> 00:35:50.730
She lost her son.

00:35:50.730 --> 00:35:56.515
And it's like any one of these
events in a life is traumatic.

00:35:56.515 --> 00:35:58.220
It will change a
person's life, right?

00:35:58.220 --> 00:36:00.530
If I have any one of these
things, I'd be bitter,

00:36:00.530 --> 00:36:02.310
be angry, I'd be revengeful.

00:36:02.310 --> 00:36:03.620
Or I would withdraw.

00:36:03.620 --> 00:36:05.920
I wouldn't do anything
in this world.

00:36:05.920 --> 00:36:09.640
And you look at Rigoberta-- she
didn't do any of those things.

00:36:09.640 --> 00:36:13.190
She's still joy, genuinely
joyful, even despite her pain.

00:36:13.190 --> 00:36:14.880
She's still serving the world.

00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:17.560
She came to Singapore
last week on invitation

00:36:17.560 --> 00:36:19.930
to speak to young people,
to inspire young people.

00:36:19.930 --> 00:36:21.820
She came all the way
here for 40 hours

00:36:21.820 --> 00:36:24.680
and flew back just to
speak to young people.

00:36:24.680 --> 00:36:26.100
And she's still working.

00:36:26.100 --> 00:36:30.970
And then going back to
fight for human rights.

00:36:30.970 --> 00:36:35.050
This amazing woman-- the
question I had for her,

00:36:35.050 --> 00:36:37.650
how do you do this?

00:36:37.650 --> 00:36:40.490
And I realized what happened.

00:36:40.490 --> 00:36:42.960
So the way she did
it was, I mean,

00:36:42.960 --> 00:36:44.930
my own explanation of
it, not her exact words,

00:36:44.930 --> 00:36:47.960
my own explanation
is she's using joy

00:36:47.960 --> 00:36:51.280
as a container for her pain.

00:36:51.280 --> 00:36:54.272
And an analogy I use is
like having a fracture.

00:36:54.272 --> 00:36:56.730
You have a very bad fracture,
a broken leg, what do you do?

00:36:56.730 --> 00:36:58.920
You put a cast around it.

00:36:58.920 --> 00:37:00.599
And the cast around
it, what does it do?

00:37:00.599 --> 00:37:01.390
It does two things.

00:37:01.390 --> 00:37:05.280
First, it limits further
damage, and secondly, it

00:37:05.280 --> 00:37:08.660
allows time to heal,
allows healing to happen.

00:37:08.660 --> 00:37:10.260
And she's doing the same thing.

00:37:10.260 --> 00:37:15.370
She's using her joy, her genuine
joy as a container for pain,

00:37:15.370 --> 00:37:17.110
so pain doesn't
cause more damage,

00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:21.590
and she can heal
in the meantime.

00:37:21.590 --> 00:37:23.320
And it's fascinating.

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:27.060
And my own experience
dealing with joy and pain

00:37:27.060 --> 00:37:30.350
is, I feel that my joy
is like-- I always said,

00:37:30.350 --> 00:37:33.420
I feel as if I was
traversing a vast desert,

00:37:33.420 --> 00:37:36.040
and every moment of
joy is like an oasis.

00:37:36.040 --> 00:37:40.340
And without an oasis, I was not
able to navigate the desert.

00:37:40.340 --> 00:37:43.340
But with an oasis, I went for
months end to the other end.

00:37:43.340 --> 00:37:45.650
And I recovered.

00:37:45.650 --> 00:37:51.680
So this ability to access joy
in addition to a happy life,

00:37:51.680 --> 00:37:57.565
it gives you resilience in
the worst circumstances.

00:37:57.565 --> 00:37:59.190
So this is not a
practice just for you.

00:38:01.750 --> 00:38:03.300
I wrote this book,
"Joy on Demand."

00:38:11.870 --> 00:38:12.900
I wrote this book.

00:38:12.900 --> 00:38:15.379
One of my main goals is
to create the conditions

00:38:15.379 --> 00:38:16.670
for world peace in my lifetime.

00:38:16.670 --> 00:38:18.840
I mean that is my goal in
life, create the conditions

00:38:18.840 --> 00:38:20.131
for world peace in my lifetime.

00:38:20.131 --> 00:38:23.460
And this book is one of the
data points towards this.

00:38:23.460 --> 00:38:29.300
And the way I want [INAUDIBLE]
to contribute is I like to--

00:38:29.300 --> 00:38:32.010
So this book is about
joy, ostensibly.

00:38:32.010 --> 00:38:34.610
However, it's also about
two related qualities.

00:38:34.610 --> 00:38:40.410
It's about inner peace,
inner joy, compassion.

00:38:40.410 --> 00:38:45.760
I think that the trigger
point for world peace

00:38:45.760 --> 00:38:47.940
is global compassion.

00:38:47.940 --> 00:38:51.300
However, compassion has to
be sustained by inner joy.

00:38:51.300 --> 00:38:53.220
Inner joy has to be
sustained by inner peace.

00:38:53.220 --> 00:38:56.050
So all three come
together as a package.

00:38:56.050 --> 00:38:59.690
So by writing a book on
joy, and with practices

00:38:59.690 --> 00:39:02.460
that actually work, that
people can actually do,

00:39:02.460 --> 00:39:05.610
because they're easy, I'm hoping
that people will practice this,

00:39:05.610 --> 00:39:07.290
and in doing that,
they will be joyful

00:39:07.290 --> 00:39:09.130
